##
## Args options
##
@node main "Running the compiler output.."

 You may choose exactly how you run the finished executable from the
 Argument options requestor.

 At the top of the requestor are the potions fo environment, You may
 choose between Cli and WorkBench.

 if Cli is chosen, A window is opened on execution ( if there is output
 from your program ) and any arguments that you may have entered in the
 argument string gadget are passed to your program as if typed at the
 command line i.e.

 	YOUR_PROGRAM [ARG1] [ARG2] [ARG3] etc.

 if you choose to run your program in a WorkBench environment, You may add
 arguments ( As if your program had been Multi Selected from WorkBench,
 i.e.
 If you had written an Arexx program that would parse a source file,
 removing comments, Corectly formatting the text etc, By Multi selection,
 Your program will process each file consecutively, Until no further
 arguments exist )

 When you change the environment to `WB', The gadgets for WorkBench
 arguments are then enabled.
 You can simply type in the full path and name to the first program or file
 you wish to use as the argument, Once you press return, you may add
 further arguments by clicking on `U' (UP), You will see the wb_arg number
 increment.
 if you wish to delete an argument, simply click on `U' or `D' until you
 find the required argument, Clear the argument (press Right-Amiga X) and
 press return, The argument will be removed and any arguments after this
 one will be moved down.

 If you are unsure of the path to the file you wish to use as the argument,
 Simply click on the GetFile gadget to the right of the Argument string
 gadget, A filerequestor will appear allowing you to choose the file.

 You can clear any previous setup that you may have had using the Clear
 button at the bottom, ( Keyboard shortcut is DELETE )

 You can Cancel the requestor, reverting back to the previous settings
 by clicking on the Cancel button at the bottom ( Keyboard shortcut is the
 ESCAPE key )

 To use the settings you have chosen, Click on the OK button at the bottom
 ( Or use the Keyboard shortcut key which is `O' )

@endnode
